  "title": "Private Tutor |Chemistry",
  "description": "<p><strong>What you'll be doing</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Develop and deliver engaging, interactive lessons that inspire and challenge our students</li>\n  <li>Design and implement innovative teaching strategies to improve student learning and performance</li>\n  <li>Assess student progress and provide personalised feedback to help them achieve their academic goals</li>\n  <li>Collaborate with the wider teaching team to share best practices and continuously improve our curriculum</li>\n  <li>Participate in professional development opportunities to stay up-to-date with the latest teaching methodologies and subject knowledge</li>\n  <li>Contribute to the overall growth and development of our educational platform and services</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>What we're looking for</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>A bachelor's degree or a related field</li>\n  <li>Minimum 2 years of teaching experience in the secondary or JC level.</li>\n  <li>Excellent communication and interpersonal skills to engage effectively with students, parents, and colleagues</li>\n  <li>Strong organisational and time management skills to juggle multiple priorities</li>\n  <li>Passion for education and a genuine desire to make a positive impact on student lives</li>\n  <li>Proactive and adaptable, with the ability to thrive in a fast-paced, dynamic environment</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>What we offer</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Competitive remuneration package with opportunities for career advancement</li>\n  <li>Ongoing professional development and training to enhance your teaching skills</li>\n  <li>Supportive and collaborative work environment with a focus on work-life balance</li>\n  <li>Access to cutting-edge educational technology and resources to enhance your teaching</li>\n</ul>",
